Bespoke fashion designer and younger brother of Comedian AY, Yomi Casual has revealed he is recuperating and prepared to resume his business soonest. The Nation had reported the celebrity stylist was involved in a ghastly motor accident on his way home from Banana Island on Sunday June 13, 2021. His elder brother AY took to his verified Instagram account to thank God for the life of his family. He posted photo with the inscription ‘Thank You Jesus’. He wrote: “That’s what I want to say on behalf of my family.” Days after, the fashion designer announced he has recovered from the trauma he suffered from the accident. Confirming his recovery, Yomi Casual on Thursday thanked family, fans as well as friends for their love. He wrote on Instagram: “It took me 48 hours to get out from that car accident trauma. I am super grateful, guys. “I wish I had the words to express my appreciation for the calls, SMS, DMs, comments and kindness. Words cannot express my thankfulness.” He added: “I never knew I am this loved by you all. GOD BLESS YOU ALL FOR THE SHOW OF LOVE.” Yomi Casual further seized the opportunity to express his dearest desire at the moment. He added: “All I need now na urgent SUV.”